A RESOLUTION
1 Commending Fire Chief Eddie Robinson, the 2024 Georgia Fire Chief of the Year; and for
2 other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, the Georgia Association of Fire Chiefs has chosen Fire Chief Eddie Robinson
4 as the 2024 Georgia Fire Chief of the Year in recognition of his exemplary leadership and
5 dedication to both the fire service and the State of Georgia; and
6 WHEREAS, he received this distinguished honor during the 53rd Annual Firefighters
7 Recognition Day at the Georgia State Capitol, an event that celebrates excellence and
8 contributions within Georgia's fire service; and
9 WHEREAS, Chief Robinson began his fire service career in 1979 as a volunteer in his
10 hometown of Rock Hill, South Carolina, before relocating to Georgia, where he continued
11 his service with the Hickory Flat Volunteer Fire Department; and
12 WHEREAS, throughout his more than two decades with Cherokee County Fire &
13 Emergency Services, Chief Robinson has demonstrated a steadfast commitment to
14 excellence, serving as Safety Officer in 2001, Division Chief of Training in 2009, Assistant
